## AI runtime state (cache, objects, threads, graphs — all ephemeral)
**/.ai/state/

## E2E test generated knowledge (ephemeral)
tests/e2e/.ai/knowledge/
target/
tests/e2e/.ai/knowledge/agent/threads/

## Local binary scratch dir (source installables live in crates/bin/)
/bin/

## Bundle CAS + binary artifacts — fully derivable from source.
## Single source of truth: scripts/populate-bundles.sh
##   - cargo build --release of all bins
##   - install into bundles/<name>/.ai/bin/<triple>/
##   - ryeos publish bundles/<name> --key <pem> --owner <label>
## Run `./scripts/populate-bundles.sh --key <pem> --owner <label>` (or
## `./scripts/gate.sh`) after a fresh checkout. Dockerfile invokes the
## same script in the build stage.
bundles/*/.ai/objects/
bundles/*/.ai/refs/
bundles/*/.ai/bin/*/
bundles/*/PUBLISHER_TRUST.toml
!bundles/.ai/PUBLISHER_TRUST.toml

# Local daemon state from dev/test runs
.local/
